                     <interp inst="t18190526-64-off343" type="offenceSubcategory" value="housebreaking"></interp>
               feloniously breaking and entering the dwelling-house of 
                     
                        <persName id="t18190526-64-victim621" type="victimName">
                           John 
                           Pearson
                        <interp inst="t18190526-64-victim621" type="surname" value="Pearson"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18190526-64-victim621" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18190526-64-victim621" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
                     
                  , about eleven o'clock in the forenoon of the <rs id="t18190526-64-cd344" type="crimeDate">16th of May</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190526-64-off343 t18190526-64-cd344"></join> (he and others being therein), and stealing therein, three mangling-cloths, value 2 s., and one waistcoat, value 1 s., his property; two gowns, value 10 s.; two frocks, value 5 s.; four petticoats, value 5 s.; one pair of stockings, value 2 s.; six napkins, value 6 s.; two bed-gowns, value 5 s.; three aprons, value 18 d., and one handkerchief, value 1 s., the goods of 
                     <persName id="t18190526-64-person622">
                        John 
                        Lovelock
                     <interp inst="t18190526-64-person622" type="surname" value="Lovelock"></interp>
